data.name: BuildingDescription5
data.value: Lumber cut by your woodcutters is processed here. Based on its level, your sawmill can increase your lumber production by up to 25 percent.

data.name: BuildingDescription4
data.value: Your population`s food is produced here. By increasing the farm`s level, you increase its crop production.

data.name: BuildingDescription7
data.value: The iron foundry melts iron. Based on its level, your iron foundry can increase your iron production by up to 25 percent.

data.name: BuildingDescription6
data.value: The brickyard converts clay into bricks. Based on its level, your brickyard can increase your clay production by up to 25 percent.

data.name: BuildingDescription1
data.value: The woodcutter cuts down trees in order to produce lumber. The further you extend the woodcutter, the more lumber is produced

data.name: BuildingDescription3
data.value: Here miners produce the precious resource of iron. By increasing the mine`s level, you increase the iron production.

data.name: BuildingDescription2
data.value: Clay is produced here. By increasing its level, you increase the clay production.

data.name: BuildingDescription9
data.value: The bakery uses flour to make bread. In conjunction to the grain mill, the increase in crop production can go up to 50 percent in total.

data.name: BuildingDescription8
data.value: Here, your grain is ground/milled in order to produce flour. Based on its level, your Grain Mill can increase your crop production by up to 25 percent.

data.name: FarmlistVillageMustBeSelected
data.value: Farmlist village needs to be selected

data.name: BuildingDescription41
data.value: The horse drinking trough cares for the well-being of your horses and therefore increases the speed of their training. The horse drinking trough reduces the crop usage for one for the following soldiers: Equites Legati from level 10, Equites Imperatoris from level 15 and Equites Caesaris from level 20. The horse drinking trough can only be built by Romans..

data.name: BuildingDescription40
data.value: The Wonder of the World represents the pride of all architecture. Only the mightiest and richest are able to build such a master work and defend it against envious enemies. Wonders of the World can only be erected in one of the old Natarian villages. However, a construction plan is also necessary. Starting with level 50, an additional plan is needed for its completion. The second plan one has to be owned by another player in the same alliance.

data.name: BuildingDescription43
data.value: By building a makeshift wall, you can protect your village against the barbarian hordes of your enemies. The higher its level, the higher is the bonus given to your forces' defence. The makeshift wall can only be built by Huns, its defence bonus is like the Teutonic earth wall and its durability is like the Roman city wall.

data.name: BuildingDescription42
data.value: By building a stone wall, you can protect your village against the barbarian hordes of your enemies. The higher its level, the higher is the bonus given to your forces' defence. The stone wall can only be built by Egyptians, its defence bonus is like the Gaulish Palisade and its durability is like the Teutonic earth wall.

data.name: BuildingDescription45
data.value: With the Waterworks you regulate the water flow to your oases. This not only helps growing trees and crops, but is also useful for quarries and mines supplying workers with water and transporting resources. This building increases the bonus of all annexed oases. Its maximum effect on level 20 doubles the effect of oases. The Waterworks can only be built by Egyptians.

data.name: BuildingDescription44
data.value: The Command Center protects the village against enemy conquests. You can build one Command Center per village. Settlers and Senators/Chiefs/Chieftains/Nomarchs/Logades can be trained there.

data.name: BuildingDescription14
data.value: Your troops can increase their stamina at the tournament square. The further the building is upgraded the faster your troops are beyond a minimum distance of 20 squares.

data.name: BuildingDescription15
data.value: The main building is the home of the village's master builders. The higher its level, the faster your master builders complete the construction of new buildings.

data.name: BuildingDescription16
data.value: Your village's troops gather here. From here, you can send them out to conquer, attack, raid or reinforce other villages.

data.name: BuildingDescription17
data.value: At the marketplace, you can trade resources with other players. The higher its level, the more resources can be transported at the same time.

data.name: BuildingDescription10
data.value: In your warehouse, the resources lumber, clay and iron are stored. By increasing its level, you increase your warehouse's capacity.

data.name: BuildingDescription11
data.value: In the granary, the crop produced on your farms is stored. By increasing its level, you increase the granary’s capacity.

data.name: BuildingDescription13
data.value: The smithy improves the weapons and armour of your troops. By increasing its level, you can order the fabrication of even better weapons and armour.

data.name: BuildingDescription18
data.value: The embassy is a place for diplomats. The higher its level, the more options the king gains.

data.name: BuildingDescription19
data.value: In the barracks, infantry can be trained. The higher its level, the faster the troops are trained.

data.name: BuildingDescription36
data.value: The trapper protects your village with well hidden traps. This means that unwary enemies can be imprisoned and won't be able to harm your village any more.

data.name: BuildingDescription37
data.value: In the hero's mansion, you can get an overview of the surrounding oasis. Starting with building level 10, you can occupy oases with your hero and increase the resource production of your village.

data.name: BuildingDescription34
data.value: The stonemason's lodge is an expert in cutting stone. The further the building is extended the higher the stability of the village's buildings. The bonus applies to all buildings, regardless of resource fields, buildings or the wall.

data.name: BuildingDescription35
data.value: Tasty mead is brewed in the brewery and later quaffed by the soldiers during the celebrations. These drinks make your soldiers braver and stronger when attacking others (1% per level). Unfortunately, the chiefs’ power of persuasion is decreased and catapults can only do random hits. It can only be built by Teutons and only in their capital. It affects the whole empire.

data.name: BuildingDescription32
data.value: By building an earth wall, you can protect your village against the barbarian hordes of your enemies. The higher its level, the higher is the bonus given to your forces' defence.

data.name: BuildingDescription33
data.value: By building a palisade, you can protect your village against the barbarian hordes of your enemies. The higher its level, the higher is the bonus given to your forces' defence.

data.name: BuildingDescription30
data.value: The great stable allows you to build more units at the same time but they cost thrice the original amount.

data.name: BuildingDescription31
data.value: By building a city wall, you can protect your village against the barbarian hordes of your enemies. The higher its level, the higher is the bonus given to your forces' defence.

data.name: BuildingDescription38
data.value: The great warehouse has 3 times the capacity of a normal warehouse. This building can only be built in wonder of the world villages or with a special Natarian artefact.

data.name: BuildingDescription39
data.value: The great granary has 3 times the capacity of a normal granary. This building can only be built in wonder of the world villages or with a special Natarian artefact.

data.name: BuildingDescription27
data.value: The riches of your empire are kept in the treasury. Your treasury has room for only one treasure. After you have captured an artefact, it takes 24 hours on a normal server and 12 hours on a 3x speed server for the artefact to become effective.

data.name: BuildingDescription26
data.value: The King or Queen of the empire lives in the palace. Only one palace can exist in your realm at a time. You need a palace in order to proclaim a village as your capital.

data.name: BuildingDescription25
data.value: The residence is a small palace, where the king or queen lives when (s)he visits the village. The residence protects the village against enemies who want to conquer it.

data.name: BuildingDescription24
data.value: In the town hall, you can hold pompous celebrations. Such a celebration increases your culture points.

data.name: BuildingDescription23
data.value: The cranny is used to hide some of your resources when the village is attacked. These resources cannot be stolen.

data.name: BuildingDescription22
data.value: In the academy, new unit types can be researched. By increasing its level, you can order the research of better units. After you researched the units in your academy, you can train them in this village.

data.name: BuildingDescription21
data.value: Siege economyengines, like catapults and rams, can be built in the workshop. The higher its level, the faster these units are produced.

data.name: BuildingDescription20
data.value: In the stable, your cavalry is trained. The higher its level, the faster the troops are trained.

data.name: BuildingDescription29
data.value: The great barracks allows you to build more units at the same time but they cost thrice the original amount.

data.name: BuildingDescription28
data.value: In the trade office, the merchants' carts get improved and equipped with powerful horses. The higher its level, the more your merchants are able to carry.
